search_parameters.q: Paul McCartney, age, music related skills + abilities + occupations, proficiency in each, and current residence location (city, state)

text_blocks.snippet: Sir Paul McCartney is currently 83 years old (born June 18, 1942). He is widely regarded as one of the most successful and versatile musicians in history.
McCartney is a prolific multi-instrumentalist who has played over 40 instruments on various recordings.

list.snippet: Bass Guitar: His primary instrument; he is renowned for a melodic, "lead bass" style.
Vocals: Possesses a versatile tenor range spanning over four octaves, capable of both tender ballads and rock screamers.
Piano/Keyboards: Highly proficient; he played piano on iconic tracks like "Let It Be" and "Hey Jude".
Guitar: Accomplished on both acoustic and electric; he played the lead guitar solo on "Taxman".
Drums: Highly capable; he famously played drums on Beatles tracks like "Back in the U.S.S.R." and "Dear Prudence".
Songwriting: One of the most successful composers ever, with 32 No. 1 hits on the Billboard Hot 100.
Other Instruments: Proficient in mandolin, ukulele, trumpet, flugelhorn, and various percussion.
Singer-Songwriter: Core career with The Beatles, Wings, and as a solo artist.
Musician & Composer: Works across rock, pop, classical, and electronic genres.
Record & Film Producer: Produced numerous albums and documentary projects.
Businessman: Owns MPL Communications, which manages a vast music publishing catalog.
Author & Poet: Published children's books like Hey Grandude! and volumes of poetry.
Activist: Long-time advocate for animal rights and vegetarianism.

text_blocks.snippet: McCartney maintains several properties and splits his time between the UK and the US.

list.snippet: Main UK Residence: A long-time home in St. John’s Wood, London and an estate in Peasmarsh, East Sussex.
US Residences: He frequently resides in Amagansett (The Hamptons), New York with his wife, Nancy Shevell. He also maintains a residence in Beverly Hills, California.
